content: On September 26, 1993, the Atlanta Braves clinched the National League West title by defeating the Colorado Rockies 7-1 at Coors Field. This victory marked the Braves' second consecutive division title, highlighting their dominance in the early '90s. Fred McGriff contributed significantly with a home run, while Greg Maddux pitched a stellar game, solidifying his reputation as one of the league's top pitchers during this era.
